title: I Was Trafficked Through The World's Deadliest Jungle
tags: DARIEN|Darien jungle|migrants|venezuela|snake pass|elon musk|bald and bankrupt|Timmy karter|south america|adventure|travel|journalism|documentary
description: The Darien Gap known as the world's most dangerous jungle. I had heard of the Darien many years ago through National Geographic and it had both fascinated and intimidated me. I knew one day I would have to visit...When the word Darien started appearing in the news in recent years by way of the migrant crises I decided that now was the time to explore it for myself. And so myself and my good friend @TimmyKarter headed north from Medellin in search of a way across the infamous jungle, avoiding cartel and bandits, injury and tropical diseases, on an adventure with migrants from all over the world where national laws don't apply. Only the laws of the jungle.Join us as we enter...the Darien.

title: How Elon Musk‚Äôs Starlink Is Bringing In Billions For SpaceX

description: Starlink is SpaceX‚Äôs answer to providing global, high-speed internet coverage using a network of thousands of satellites buzzing around the planet in a region known as low Earth orbit (LEO), about 342 miles above the Earth‚Äôs surface. SpaceX launched its first batch of Starlink satellites back in 2019, and since then, adoption of the service has ballooned. Starlink now has over 2 million active customers and is available on all 7 continents and in over 60 countries. Starlink has been praised for its ability to connect remote parts of the world that would otherwise not have access to reliable internet. The service has also become indispensable in areas hit by natural disasters, and, more recently, during times of war, particularly the Russia-Ukraine war. But Starlink‚Äôs growing influence is garnering condemnation from some who say that SpaceX CEO, Elon Musk is meddling in geopolitics, while the scientific community is raising alarms of the effect of thousands of satellites on radio and optical astronomy.Chapters:00:00 - 03:03 Intro03:03 - 06:36 Behind Starlink‚Äôs growth06:36 - 10:33 Starlink and geopolitics10:33 - 15:35 Scientific concerns15:35 - 18:38 FutureProduced and Edited by: Magdalena PetrovaAnimation: Mallory BranganSupervising Producer: Jeniece PettittEditorial Support: Michael SheetzAdditional Footage: Getty Images¬ª Subscribe to CNBC: https://cnb.cx/SubscribeCNBC¬ª Subscribe to CNBC TV: https://cnb.cx/SubscribeCNBCtelevisionAbout CNBC: From 'Wall Street' to 'Main Street' to award winning original documentaries and Reality TV series, CNBC has you covered. description: Now and Then's eventful journey to fruition took place over five decades and is the product of conversations and collaborations between the four Beatles that go on to this day. The long mythologised John Lennon demo was first worked on in February 1995 by Paul, George and Ringo as part of The Beatles Anthology project but it remained unfinished, partly because of the impossible technological challenges involved in working with the vocal John had recorded on tape in the 1970s. For years it looked like the song could never be completed. But in 2022 there was a stroke of serendipity. A software system developed by Peter Jackson and his team, used throughout the production of the documentary series Get Back, finally opened the way for the uncoupling of John‚Äôs vocal from his piano part. As a result, the original recording could be brought to life and worked on anew with contributions from all four Beatles. This remarkable story of musical archaeology reflects The Beatles‚Äô endless creative curiosity and shared fascination with technology. It marks the completion of the last recording that John, Paul and George and Ringo will get to make together and celebrates the legacy of the foremost and most influential band in popular music history.Video Director: Peter JacksonVideo Producers: Peter Jackson, Clare Olssen, Jonathan ClydeAudio Producers: Paul McCartney and Giles MartinProduction Company: WingNut Films Productions LtdOrder/Listen to Now And Then: https://TheBeatles.lnk.to/NowAndThenYTOrder/Listen to Red and Blue: https://TheBeatles.lnk.to/RedAndBlue2023YTWatch more videos from The Beatles: https://thebeatles.lnk.to/YTPlaylists Subscribe to The Beatles‚Äô YouTube channel & ring the bell to never miss a new video: https://thebeatles.lnk.to/YTSignup Sign up for The Beatles‚Äô Official Email List: https://www.thebeatles.com/newsletter   Stream The Beatles: üéôÔ∏è Apple Music: https://thebeatles.lnk.to/stream/AppleMusic üéôÔ∏è Spotify: https://thebeatles.lnk.to/stream/Spotify üéôÔ∏è Amazon Music: https://thebeatles.lnk.to/stream/AmazonMusic üéôÔ∏è Pandora: https://thebeatles.lnk.to/stream/Pandora üéôÔ∏è Tidal: https://thebeatles.lnk.to/stream/Tidal üéôÔ∏è Deezer: https://thebeatles.lnk.to/stream/Deezer üéôÔ∏è YouTube Music: https://thebeatles.lnk.to/stream/YouTubeMusic   Follow The Beatles:  ‚≠ê https://www.thebeatles.com ‚≠ê https://www.instagram.com/thebeatles‚≠ê https://www.facebook.com/thebeatles‚≠ê https://www.tiktok.com/@thebeatles‚≠ê https://twitter.com/thebeatles #TheBeatles #NowAndThen #JohnLennon #PaulMcCartney #GeorgeHarrison #RingoStarr

80gRecipe:360g potatoesDice the potatoesMove to a pot600ml waterCook for 15 minutes on medium high heat100ml water100ml milk12g white sugar3g active dry yeastMix and wait for 5 minutes300g all purpose or bread flour3g saltMix well15ml olive oilKnead the dough until smoothContinue to knead the doughCover and rest for 15 minutesDrain the water from the potatoesSalt28g unsalted butterMash the potatoesDivide into 8 partsAfter 15 minutesDivide the dough into 8 partsTake each piece of dough and shape into a ballRepeatCover and rest for 10-15 minutes80g cheddar cheeseTake one section of the mashed potatoShape into a ballCreate a divot in the centerPut some shredded cheese in the centerCover up the cheese with the potatoRepeatAfter letting the dough restFlatten the dough with a rolling title: the end of this chapter (important announcement)
tags: [none]
description: I started developing the Sunee App and brand in 2018, at a time where my career and building my business was my main focus and drive. Before I was a mother and a wife I felt such a sense of purpose and passion pouring all of my time into work.Now in 2023, a lot has changed. Priorities have shifted, business goals have been refined and most importantly, I have become a wife and a mother. This season of motherhood has been my greatest blessing and an experience I know is fleeting. In our life there is time to do everything, but not all at once. With all of this in mind and my intentions to create more balance in my life, I have come to the decision to close down the Sunee App. When I work on a project or product, I will give it my all and nothing less. Considering all avenues and possibilities for the app's future, the decision to close the app has been one that has given me the greatest sense of peace.In saying this, this has not been a decision I have made lightly as I know how special and impactful Sunee and our recipes are to so many of you. I want to take this moment to sincerely thank every single one of you who have supported Sunee. None of this would have been possible without you and I‚Äôm so grateful that you have been along for this amazing journey!While the app will no longer exist, this is not goodbye. My passion for creating healthy recipes is deeper than ever, however, my approach and pace will now honour my season. The experience of creating my cookbook was the confirmation I needed to acknowledge that right now in my life, I need to be working on a project basis.. This allows me to pour all of my creativity into my work, whilst prioritising my role as a mother and raising my boys.Again, thank you all for your support and love.For more details on the closure of the Sunee app head to www.sunee.com/closing
